 30→/// Browser automation tool for interacting with web pages.
 31→///
 32→/// Unlike `web_fetch` which just retrieves page content, this tool allows
 33→/// full browser interaction: clicking buttons, filling forms, taking
 34→/// screenshots, and executing JavaScript.
 35→///
 36→/// This tool automatically tracks and reuses browser session IDs. When
 37→/// the LLM doesn't provide a session_id (or provides empty string), the
 38→/// tool will reuse the most recently created browser session for the current
 39→/// chat session. This prevents pool exhaustion without leaking browser state
